## Example 7 — Real-World Point-Slope Applications

**25. SALES** Light trucks sold: 5.919 million in 2011, 11.055 million in 2017. Write an equation for y trucks sold x years after 2010.

2011 is x = 1, y = 5.919. 2017 is x = 7, y = 11.055.

[m = (11.055 - 5.919)/(7 - 1) = 5.136/6 = 0.856]

Using point (1, 5.919): [y - 5.919 = 0.856(x - 1)]

